reviews.text: Very down to earth eatery, with basic tables and stools.  Food is served on a tray, the portions are decent and the food is nice. More of an eat and go place than a chill with friends eatery.
Very decent quality and compared to other chains, rice drink is a plus
Korean fast food, not much service needed and given. Food quality is great for the price you give. Cheap meals in such a crowded busy district in Causeway Bay.

Pricey for a bibibamp 49 hkd but I guess it's because the restaurant is in Causeway Bay. The meat comes cold but the rock boll is a sizzling hot plate so the meat gets hot by the plate. The taste is quite bland. Hopefully, there is the hot sauce.

I ordered the spicy chicken with rice option, and it was tasty! (at least compared to other korean options in HK) The sauce is not super spicy and gives a great kick of flavour. Also a fine amount of vegetables in the dish. Decently priced for Korean food in the cwb area.
(We also ordered the dduk bok gi, didn't get a pic of it; tasted good but was of quite a small serving.)
